-- Mexico Equity Movers: Alfa, America Movil, Homex Were Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-08-20T21:29:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-20/mexico-equity-movers-alfa-america-movil-homex-were-active.html
IPC (MEXBOL)  index falls 0.5% at market close
in Mexico City, with 14 shrs rising, 19 falling and two little
changed.  ADVANCERS:  *  Desarrolladora Homex (HOMEX*)   +4.2%; price closed at two-
week low on Aug. 17
*  Empresas ICA (ICA*)   +0.9%; CEO Alonso Quintana says company
exploring strategic alternatives for homebuilding unit  DECLINERS:  *  Alfa (ALFAA)   -0.9%; down 6.5% in past three days, most
since July 23, after touching record high on Aug. 15
*  America Movil (AMXL)   -0.3%; Mexico’s Supreme Court declined
on Aug. 7 to review a suit by unit Telefonos de Mexico against
Mexico’s communications ministry, a court official who asked not
to be named under the agency’s policy said Aug. 17
* Axtel (AXTELCPO MM) -6%; leaving IPC index Sept. 3 in
rebalancing
*  Consorcio Ara (ARA*)   -2.1%; also leaving IPC index Sept. 3
in rebalancing  To contact the reporter on this story:
